title: Sources: Embiid's participation to be investigated
description: The NBA is likely to begin an investigation later this week into the Philadelphia 76ers surrounding the player participation of All-NBA center Joel Embiid, sources told ESPN on Wednesday.
author: Shams Charania

title: Hill: Tua's return to field 'almost made me cry'
description: Tyreek Hill called Tua Tagovailoa's return to Dolphins practice Wednesday "beautiful." "Almost made me cry today like just having him in the lineup, having him call the plays, having him direct the offense, like just hearing his voice," the wideout said.
author: Marcel Louis-Jacques

title: 'Kids will be trying that in the playground' - Haaland goal hailed
description: Erling Haaland's "amazing" acrobatic backheel volley for Manchester City against Sparta Prague on Wednesday left many of those who saw it live "speechless".

title: 'Almost unbeatable' - so will Liverpool turn wins and records into trophies?
description: Liverpool boss Arne Slot says records are nice but he would rather have trophies after his side's 11th win in 12 games.

description: The concussion was at least McCall's second in the last 13 months.

title: Wakefield return to Super League under grading criteria
description: Wakefield Trinity will return to Super League for the 2025 season following the release of IMG's gradings, with London Broncos dropping into the Championship.

title: Fury's wife suffered miscarriage day before Usyk fight
description: Tyson Fury has revealed he was struck by personal tragedy on the eve of his first fight with Oleksandr Usyk, before only learning of his wife's miscarriage when he returned home.
